      "content": "idk i just dont want to pay for a clinic visit if i dont have to... i read online that medical grade honey is actually used in hospitals to heal wounds and kill bacteria. if i just clean it real well and use a thick layer of honey, could that work instead of going in? it doesnt look that bad once i stop the initial bleeding.",
